Fundamental Articles
----field----
field: {00E1D306-96BD-4B32-85B4-CD63C53CC6C1}
name: Abstract
key: abstract
content-length: 122

This set of articles is to set the foundation of key Sitecore concepts and also to get familiar with Sitecore terminology.
----field----
field: {5A5684BB-8B54-44F6-ABCC-2BADA05ADA5D}
name: Body
key: body
content-length: 2185

<p>Key to understanding Sitecore and its advantages to solving your web content needs and challenges are the core features and architectural underpinnings of the platform.</p>
<p>This Launch Sitecore site has been designed as both an implementation example, as well as a resource itself with many articles and examples. The fundamental concepts, on which you will build greater understanding include:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="~/link.aspx?_id=46E758489D9247E9A5AA40A64B689E4D&amp;_z=z">The Launch Sitecore site.</a> <br />
  An in-depth explanation of this site, the articles, and the implementation itself which you can use and learn from.
  </li>
  <li><a href="~/link.aspx?_id=C4E0EF5C1DDF46848CADEED50971237F&amp;_z=z">The Sitecore User Interfaces</a><br />
  Since there are many different roles and user types in a large Web CMS implementation, Sitecore provides a number of interfaces designed for different tasks.
  </li>
  <li><a href="~/link.aspx?_id=07DAF0C219924C0ABB7F92A700E97FF4&amp;_z=z">What is Content?</a><br />
  As a content-based Web CMS, a proper content structure and information architecture is key to a successful implementation. This explains the key concepts of data templates, inheritance and information architecture.
  </li>
  <li><a href="~/link.aspx?_id=5EA97F1D068546379D3DD4F289BA7950&amp;_z=z">What is Presentation?</a><br />
  Sitecore gives you a solid framework and full control of your presentation layer code. This article gives some of the key concepts for building your presentation layer.
  </li>
  <li><a href="~/link.aspx?_id=68DAE74D1B6D4411967BCD80321355D3&amp;_z=z">Binding Content and Presentation</a><br />
  Sitecore has a number of different methods for binding content and presentation. Through static binding, template defaults, placeholders, and permissions, you can easily provide the right balance between flexibility and structure, while also minimising the tasks on your content creators.
  </li>
  <li><a href="~/link.aspx?_id=98205BE9FBD042BC8034B428B53D6CBD&amp;_z=z">Sitecore Architecture</a><br />
  An overview of "typical" implementations and the purposes of the various databases on which Sitecore is built. </li>
</ul>
